ast.name: Synapse
ast.comment:
Synapse lets you capture memories of your experiences, gathers as much information as possible and makes the pictures searchable. This means you can take a picture of a research paper (or printer model or a particular logo) and find it after one or two months by providing Synapse with hints (or keywords or an optional set of tags that you assigned during creation).

Try it today to see what Synapse will help you find within your memories... Every memory you collect will earn you a point. Earn sufficient points and become a leaderboard-synaptic!

Note: Visual recognition currently works ok with titles of research papers, artwork, regular text, business cards, landmarks and logos. It is destined to fail on chairs, tables and pencils :-)
